<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicName LSID="38CD0A57-2CF3-516E-AE49-4A60B0331D0B" authority="R. M. King &amp; H. Rob., Phytologia 25: 66. 1972" authorityName="R. M. King &amp; H. Rob., Phytologia 25: 66." authorityYear="1972" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Ophryosporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ophryosporus anomalus" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="anomalus">Ophryosporus anomalus R.M.King &amp; H.Rob., Phytologia 25: 66. 1972</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
Typonym: 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Piqueria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Piqueria cumingii" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cumingii">Piqueria cumingii</taxonomicName>
B.L.Rob., Proc. Amer. Acad. Arts, 42: 11. 1906, non 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Ophryosporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ophryosporus cumingii" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cumingii">Ophryosporus cumingii</taxonomicName>
Benth. ex Baker (1895: 188, based on 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Mandon 264</emphasis>
from Bolivia.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
Chile. Region I 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Tarapacá">Tarapaca</normalizedToken>
and Region II Antofagasta: &quot;Peruvia meridionalis: Cobija, Iquiqui et Arica&quot;, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">H.Cuming 953</emphasis>
(lectotype, selected by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.31055/1851.2372.v48.n2.6267" author="Plos, A" journalOrPublisher="Boletin de la Sociedad Argentina de Botanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="335 - 340" refId="B13" refString="Plos, A, Sancho, G, 2013. Lectotipificaciones en Ophryosporus (Asteraceae, Eupatorieae, Critoniinae). Boletin de la Sociedad Argentina de Botanica 48 (2): 335 - 340, DOI: https://doi.org/10.31055/1851.2372.v48.n2.6267" title="Lectotipificaciones en Ophryosporus (Asteraceae, Eupatorieae, Critoniinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.31055/1851.2372.v48.n2.6267" volume="48" year="2013">Plos and Sancho (2013</bibRefCitation>
: 338): K [K000486684, photo!]; isolectotypes E [E00322766, photo!], GH [GH00010778!], K [K000486685, photo!], P [P02673192, photo!]); remaining syntypes: 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Gaudichaud</emphasis>
s.n. (B [probably destroyed, could not be found], F [F1012247, photo!]).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Ophryosporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ophryosporus anomalus" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="anomalus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Ophryosporus anomalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been cited for Peru (
<bibRefCitation author="King, RM" journalOrPublisher="Phytologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="65 - 67" refId="B7" refString="King, RM, Robinson, H, 1972b. Studies in the Eupatorieae (Asteraceae). CXI. Additions to the genus Ophryosporus. Phytologia 25: 65 - 67" title="Studies in the Eupatorieae (Asteraceae). CXI. Additions to the genus Ophryosporus." volume="25" year="1972 b">King and Robinson 1972b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Brako, L" journalOrPublisher="Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="1 - 1286" refId="B1" refString="Brako, L, Zarucchi, JL, 1993. Catalogue of the flowering plants and gymnosperms of Peru. Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 45: 1 - 1286" title="Catalogue of the flowering plants and gymnosperms of Peru." volume="45" year="1993">Brako and Zarucchi 1993</bibRefCitation>
), likely due to the type collection label (&quot;Peruvia meridionalis...&quot;). However, the localities mentioned there (&quot;...Cobija, Iquiqui et Arica&quot;) are now situated in Chile, and all other reports originate from the coastal zone around Tocopilla (
<bibRefCitation author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Revista Chilena de Historia Natural" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="4 - 8" refId="B5" refString="Johnston, IM, 1932. New records for the flora of the Nitrate Coast. Revista Chilena de Historia Natural 36: 4 - 8" title="New records for the flora of the Nitrate Coast." volume="36" year="1932">Johnston 1932</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Jaffuel, PF" journalOrPublisher="Revista Chilena de Historia Natural" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="265 - 274" refId="B3" refString="Jaffuel, PF, 1936. Excursiones botanicas a los alrededores de Tocopilla. Revista Chilena de Historia Natural 40: 265 - 274" title="Excursiones botanicas a los alrededores de Tocopilla." volume="40" year="1936">Jaffuel 1936</bibRefCitation>
) and therefore 
<bibRefCitation author="Luebert, F" journalOrPublisher="Boletin del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="27 - 52" refId="B9" refString="Luebert, F, Garcia, N, Schulz, N, 2007. Observaciones sobre la flora y vegetacion de los alrededores de Tocopilla (22°S, Chile). Boletin del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural 56: 27 - 52" title="Observaciones sobre la flora y vegetacion de los alrededores de Tocopilla (22 ° S, Chile)." volume="56" year="2007">Luebert et al. (2007)</bibRefCitation>
considered it a Chilean endemic. We hereby extend the distribution of the species to include the populations from the coastal area between 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Río">Rio</normalizedToken>
Loa and Iquique, previously referred to as 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. floribundus" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" rank="species" species="floribundus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">O. floribundus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.4067/S0716-078X2001000200014" author="Munoz-Schick, M" journalOrPublisher="Revista Chilena de Historia Natural" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="389 - 405" refId="B10" refString="Munoz-Schick, M, Pinto, R, Mesa, A, Moreira-Munoz, A, 2001. &quot;Oasis de neblina&quot; en los cerros costeros del sur de Iquique, region de Tarapaca, Chile, durante el evento El Nino 1997-1998. Revista Chilena de Historia Natural 74 (2): 389 - 405, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4067/S0716-078X2001000200014" title="&quot; Oasis de neblina &quot; en los cerros costeros del sur de Iquique, region de Tarapaca, Chile, durante el evento El Nino 1997 - 1998." url="https://doi.org/10.4067/S0716-078X2001000200014" volume="74" year="2001">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Muñoz-Schick">Munoz-Schick</normalizedToken>
et al. 2001
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.4067/S0717-66432009000100004" author="Pinto, R" journalOrPublisher="Botanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="28 - 49" refId="B11" refString="Pinto, R, Luebert, F, 2009. Datos sobre la flora vascular del desierto costero de Arica y Tarapaca, Chile, y sus relaciones fitogeograficas con el sur de Peru. Gayana. Botanica 66 (1): 28 - 49, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4067/S0717-66432009000100004" title="Datos sobre la flora vascular del desierto costero de Arica y Tarapaca, Chile, y sus relaciones fitogeograficas con el sur de Peru. Gayana." url="https://doi.org/10.4067/S0717-66432009000100004" volume="66" year="2009">Pinto and Luebert 2009</bibRefCitation>
). See discussion below under the latter species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
